.TH TTF2LFF 1 "June 2025" "Debian GNU/Linux"
.SH NAME
ttf2lff \- TrueType to LibreCAD Font Format (LFF) converter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ttf2lff
[\fIoptions\fR] \fIinput.ttf output.lff\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ttf2lff
converts fonts in TrueType format (.ttf, .otf) to LibreCAD Font Format (LFF).
The LFF format is used by LibreCAD for vector fonts in drawings.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-nodes " \fIN\fR"
Number of nodes for quadratic and cubic spline approximation (default: 4)
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-author " \fITEXT\fR"
Author name for font metadata
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-letterspacing " \fIN\fR"
Letter spacing (default: 3.0)
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-wordspacing " \fIN\fR"
Word spacing (default: 6.75)
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-linespacing " \fIN\fR"
Line spacing factor (default: 1.0)
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-precision " \fIN\fR"
Number of decimal digits (default: 6)
.TP
.BR \-L ", " \-\-license " \fITEXT\fR"
Font license

.SS "Tuning Options (from python-lff)"
.TP
.BR \-z ", " \-\-zerovector
Remove duplicate consecutive vertices. This eliminates redundant points that can occur from bezier curve approximations.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-round
Round vertex coordinates to a grid. Use with \fB\-g\fR to set grid size.
.TP
.BR \-g ", " \-\-grid " \fIN\fR"
Grid size for vertex rounding (default: 0.0001)
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-mergepath
Merge paths that share the same start/end vertex. This combines adjacent polylines.
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-nestedchar
Analyze for nested characters (glyphs that could reference other glyphs).
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-nocomment
Remove comments from glyph definitions.
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-tuning
Apply all tuning options at once.

.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message and exit.

.SH EXAMPLE
Convert a font with default settings:
.PP
.nf
.B ttf2lff input.ttf output.lff
.fi
.PP

Convert with all tuning options enabled:
.PP
.nf
.B ttf2lff \-\-tuning \-\-author "John Doe" input.ttf output.lff
.fi
.PP

Convert with specific tuning options:
.PP
.nf
.B ttf2lff -a "Jane Smith" -n 8 -z -r -g 0.001 -m input.ttf output.lff
.fi

.SH "LFF FORMAT"
The LibreCAD Font Format (LFF) is a vector font format.
Each glyph consists of polylines with vertices separated by semicolons.
Coordinates are comma-separated x,y values.

Example glyph:
.PP
.nf
[#0041] A
0,0;3,9;6,9
1,0;4,0
.fi

.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR librecad (1)
.PP
LFF Font Format specification: https://github.com/LibreCAD/LibreCAD/wiki/LFF-Font-Format
